{{Infobox person |image = Le%C3%B3n_Dujovne.jpg |image_caption = León Dujovne in 1971. |birth_date = 15 November 1898 |birth_place = [[Kurilovich]], [[Russian Empire]] (present-day [[Ukraine]]) |death_date = {{Death date and age|1984|1|16|1898|11|15|df=y}} |death_place = [[Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]] }} '''León Dujovne''' (15 November 1898 – 16 January 1984) was an [[Argentine]] writer, philosopher, essayist and journalist.
== Early life == Dujovne was born to [[History of the Jews in Ukraine|Ukrainian-Jewish]] parents in the village of Kurilovich, near the small town of [[Mohyliv-Podilskyi]] ([[Vinnytsia Oblast]]), on the border with [[Bessarabia]] (Moldova). At the age of one, his parents emigrated to [[Argentina]]; the family settled in [[Basavilbaso]], [[Entre Ríos Province|Entre Ríos]], one of the several [[History of the Jews in Argentina|Jewish colonies]] founded by Baron [[Maurice de Hirsch]] in the province.<ref name=Sarmiento>León Dujovne: [http://www.raoulwallenberg.net/wp-content/files_flutter/1296225734ebookdujovnesarmienRosarino, ''La filosofía de la Historia de Sarmiento''], publicación póstuma, en homenaje al 20<sup>o</sup> aniversario de su fallecimiento. Prólogo de Félix Gustavo Schuster y nota biográfica detallada de Celina A. Lértora Mendoza. Buenos Aires: Universidad Nacional de Buenos Aires, Facultad de Filosofía y Letras, 2005.</ref>
