{{Other people|William Hatch}} {{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
'''William Henry Paine Hatch''' (August 2, 1875 &ndash; November 11, 1972) was an [[United States|American]] theologian and [[New Testament]] scholar, born at [[Camden, New Jersey|Camden, N. J.]] He attended [[Harvard University|Harvard]], graduating in 1898 (Ph.D., 1904). Afterward, he graduated the [[Episcopal Divinity School|Episcopal Theological School]] in [[Cambridge, Massachusetts]], and the [[General Theological Seminary]] in [[City of New York|New York City]]. He was ordained to the [[Episcopal Church in the United States of America|Episcopal]] priesthood in 1902. Hatch was awarded a [[Doctor of Divinity]] from [[Union Theological Seminary (New York City)|Union Theological Seminary]] in New York and a D.Théol. from the [[University of Strasbourg]]. He was Professor of the Literature and Interpretation of the New Testament at the [[Episcopal Divinity School|Episcopal Theological School]] in [[Cambridge, Massachusetts]]. Hatch published many articles and reviews and was the author of ''The Pauline Idea of Faith'' (1917), and, with C. C. Edmunds, ''The Gospel Manuscripts of the General Theological Seminary'' (1918).
== Works ==
* W. H. P. Hatch, [https://books.google.com/books?id=ZbjhSQAACAAJ&dq=Hatch,+%22The+Principal+Uncial+Manuscripts+of+the+New+Testament%22&hl=pl&sa=X&ei=CX8QT-2rNYbvsgaD7fg4&ved=0CFQQ6AEwBjgK ''The Principal Uncial Manuscripts of the New Testament''] (Chicago, 1939). * W. H. P. Hatch (1946). [https://books.google.com/books?id=3-aPhD7jem4C&printsec=frontcover&hl=#v#page=54 ''An album of dated Syriac manuscripts''. Boston: The American Academy of Arts and Sciences], reprinted in 2002 by Gorgias Press. {{ISBN|1-931956-53-7}}. * W. H. P. Hatch, [https://books.google.com/books?id=TXEPAQAAMAAJ&q= ''Facsimiles and descriptions of minuscule manuscripts of the New Testament''] (Cambridge, 1951). * [[Charles Carroll Edmunds|C. C. Edmunds]], and W. H. P. Hatch, [https://archive.org/stream/cu31924009680830#page/n7/mode/2up ''The Gospel Manuscripts of the General Theological Seminary''], HTS 4 (1918), pp.&nbsp;7, 50-68.
